    public class HttpConnector
extends Node
    *

    HttpConnector Component

    Component:

    Name:

    		 HttpConnector

    Category:

    		 Others

    Description:

    		 Component provides a functionality for sending http requests. URL can be set or retrieved from input port. Implemented http methods are GET and POST. Place holders can be used at URL when input port is connected. The format of placeholder is *{placeholder_name}. Input fields not used for substitution of placeholders can be added to the URL as parameters (they can be add to the query string or method body if the POST method is used. Ignored fields specify which input fields can't be add as parameters. If POST method is used input fields can be added as multipart entities. Component allows HTTP Authentication (basic and digest). Authentication is proceed if username and password is set.)

    type "HTTP_CONNECTOR"
    url URL for http request. Place holders can be used when input port is connected. Place holder format is *{}
    urlInputField URL for http request from metadata field. Place holders can be used.
    requestMethod Http request method. Can be DELETE, GET, HEAD, OPTIONS, PATCH, POST, PUT, TRACE.
    addInputFieldsAsParametres Specifies whether parameters are added to the URL. (values: true/false)
    addInputFieldsAsParametresTo Specifies whether input fields should be add to the query string or method body. Parameters can be added to the method body in case that POST method is used. (values: Query/Body)
    ignoredFields Specifies which input fields aren't added as parameters. List of input fields separated by ; is expected.
    multipartEntities Specifies which input fields are added to the request as multipart entities. Multipart entities can be added to the request in case that POST method is used. List of input fields separated by ; is expected.
    headerProperties Additional http header properties.
    charset Character encoding of the output file (if not specified, then ISO-8859-1 is used)
    inputField The input field whose content is sent as the request.
    requestContent The text field whose content is sent as the request.
    inFileUrl Input file.
    outFileUrl Output file.
    append Whether to append data at the end if output file exists or replace it (values: true/false)
    authenticationMethod HTTP Authentication method. Authentication is done if username and password is entered. (values: BASIC/DIGEST/ANY)
    username Username for http authentication
    password Password for http authentication
    consumerKey Consumer key to be used with OAuth authentication
    consumerSecret Consumer secret to be used with OAuth authentication
    responseAsFileName If specified, the component will write response to a temporary file and send the file name in output field User can then read with "indirect" reading. If not specified, the response is passed by value. (values true/false)
    responseDirectory Directory for response files.
    responseFilePrefix Prefix for response files
